Oct 30 2009 	Fantastic Location Budget at its best	I stayed for 5 nights at Hotel Meridiana and had a great time in London. The best part of this hotel is the location, and the value for money. It is just a couple of minutes walk from Kings Cross &amp; St Pancras stations and the London Tube. There are plenty of cheap places to eat and shop nearby, and even a laundry not far away. I booked a single room with share bathroom. The room was small, but had everything I needed including a sink in the room, a TV, kettle and coffee. Plenty of room to store things, and the bed was comfortable. The only issue I had was the floor in the room was on a bit of a slope (and the bed wasn't level). Easy fixed by putting a bar of soap under the legs of the bed! The price was cheap, and the room and share bathroom were always cleaned every day. The staff were very helpful and friendly, and are happy for you to leave your bags at reception to be picked up later in the day after check out. Internet is only available by plugging in while sitting on the couch in reception, but I never had to wait for it become available, and it was fast and free! Breakfast was also great, and the service wonderful. The local area was safe and quite, and I'd highly recommend this hotel to anyone not wanting to spend their whole travel budget on expensive London hotels! It was also great to know after a long day of sightseeing I could be off the tube and in my room in under 5 minutes!	
