Jun 11 2008 	Good value for money	Me, my mom and my sister stayed at the Hotel Meridiana for just a weekend at the end of May. Because we were only staying for the wekend, we decided to save some money and get a triple room with shared facilities. The good stuff: The hotel is located SO close to King's Cross, but you still can't hear all the traffic and ppl, because it's in Argyle Square. The rooms are nice and clean (a bit small maybe - but that's just London!), and the beds are a bit hard but still comforable. The owners are nice and helpfull when asking for advice. There are three shared showers, and we never had to stand in line. The rooms have sinks and tv's. The rooms are cheap!The less good stuff: Like so many other small London hotels, we had to lug our luggage up a narrow and steep staircase. The breakfast could be better, like a buffet, but there isn't room for that. The walls are very thin and if you're a light sleeper (like me), it can be very difficult to sleep when there's ppl walking back and forth in the hallway (earplugs helped).However, the good stuff (especially the price) make up for the less good, and I would definitly recommend the hotel to others, and stay there again myself.	
