Oct 18 2007 	No frills but good deal for London	Meridiana was good for a tight budget in London. The en suite room was spartan, with just the basic bed-closet-tiny bathroom-dresser, but quiet and clean. Considering that the cost was 1/2 the price of the chain hotel up the block, it was a great deal. The property is more like a &quot;micro-hotel&quot; than what you would expect as a more personal &quot;B&amp;B&quot; in other parts of the UK. However, the staff was friendly, especially the reception desk. They were eager to give us everything we needed during our stay and were quite cheery. Expect the traditional &quot;Engish Breakfast&quot;, with eggs/bacon/sausage/toast/juice, in a smallish dining room. You may have to wait for a table and/or share with housemates. Beware the sausage! The location was ideal for us - on a little square full of similiar properties, two blocks walk from King's Cross Station. This put London only about 10 minutes away by tube, and the train station is right next door to the Underground station. Be sure you don't miss the British Library, just a few blocks away. They have orignal documents on display like the Gutenburg Bible, work from WIlliam Blake, and even Mozart and the Beatles. You can also visit Platform 9 3/4 in King's Cross if you're a Harry Potter fan. We liked our stay at Meridiana and would consider them again if we return to London.	
