Jan 13 2007 	Great Value A Bit Dingy	Hotel Meridiana is amazingly affordable for London-- L58 for a 2-person en suite room. And the location is great-- 2 minutes walk from King's Cross underground station, so we were able to get anywhere in London within 30 minutes. The surrounding neighborhood is pretty lively, even late at night-- I was never the only person on the street, even coming home at midnight. However, several times I had to pass through clouds of pot smoke on the surrounding streets, which is a bit disconcerting. I never felt unsafe, but I did have my guard up just like I would in an American city. Our room was in the basement and smelled faintly of mildew-- there were some spots in the shower-- and the carpet looked pretty grimy. But the sheets were clean and the bed was comfortable. The full English breakfast was more than I could eat-- I stuck to corn flakes and toast. The breakfast room is small, but the staff are very quick and efficient and make sure that everyone gets served, even if it's after breakfast hours when you get seated. On balance, this was a great value for 3 nights. But I think if I were staying longer, the dinginess of the basement room would wear on me.	
