Jul 9 2006	cosy and convient	My husband and I spent one night at this hotel. The location is excellent, minutes from Kings cross. The area is quiet. The staff were friendly and helpful. We stayed in room 2, which was ensuite. The room wasnt huge but enough just for two. There is tea/coffee making facitilies, we bought some milk as there was only milk powder sachets. The room had a cosy feel to it and the bed was comfy. The bathroom was a little bit small, but was clean and everything worked ok. It was adquate for us and would stay there again if we decided to come to london again for a break.	
Jun 30 2006	Not Suitable for old lads	good location, very close to King's cross station.. the room was adequate, we didn't stay at the en-suite room, and this sometimes caused problems as we had to share one bathroom with other 16 people in one floor. Really not recommended for elderly people if you have to stay at 2nd or 3rd floor. the stairs are quite steep and if you have knee problem like me, You know what Im talking about (I stayed at 3rd floor). The people are nice and friendly, but they couldn't do anything to get me moved to lower room as It was peak season. Overall, good room, proper facilities (towels and tea), clean bathroom (although the water pressure was so frustating). we didn't experience the breakast there (the breakfast room always full). better not stay there on summer	
Jun 6 2006	Pleasant little hotel	2 minute walk from Kings Cross, bus stop close by with buses that run frequently and every 10 minutes throughout the night. The hotel is very clean which is always our main concern. The room was small but sufficient with a little shower room. You may have to share a table at breakfast time, but the staff are pleasant and food nice. The hotel is very reasonably priced and was more than sufficient for our 2 night stay in London before we jetted off on honeymoon. We are planning on booking this hotel on our next trip to London.	
