Feb 12 2006	Great place	My husband and me spent three nights at the Hotel Meridiana, and it was great. We stayed at an en-suite room, not very big but enough for two people, very clean and nice, with TV and tea arrangements, and the bathroom was good, with clean towels every day.The english breakfast was good enough, made at the moment, and complete. The placewas pleasant and the staff was very kind. And, of course, only two minutes walking to King's Cross, where you find 6 underground lines and trains. In short, it is a Hotel with an excellent quality/price relation.	
Nov 25 2004	Watch-out protect your vacation memories	I made a reservation for this hotel for our family vacation in London. Unfortunately, we have to cancel our trip to London. The Hotel refused to return my deposit, even though I cancelled the reservation two weeks ahead of time. We don't have any plans to vacation in London in the future. So, we consider this as stealing at broad day light and with impunity.	
Feb 21 2004	Great Location and Value	We stayed five nights at the Hotel Meridiana in February 2004. We had decided that we wanted to stay in a budget hotel so that we could spend our money on dining, attractions, day trips, etc. We got a non-en-suite double for only 37.5 pounds per night...one of the cheapest deals I could find on the Internet. The hotel was at Argyle Square near Kings Cross station, and, as a previous reviewer noted, this is a great location. It is about a two minute walk to the Kings Cross station, and the Underground links to about 5 different lines from this station so you can get just about anywhere in London very easily. There are a lot of other hotels around the area, it was well lit, and we felt safe walking around the area, even at night. The hotel itself was nothing special, but a good value for what we paid. The bed was a little firm, but manageable, and the shared bathroom facilities were clean. The bedroom had its own pedestal sink and tile backsplash and quaint country furniture. There was no telephone in the room, but a 13 inch color television with good reception. The staff was friendly and helpful...they even let us check in early, about 11:00 am, on our arrival date (since our flight from Atlanta got in early in the morning, we were exhausted from the trip, so it was nice not to have to wait until 2:00 pm). The previous reviewer's description of the breakfast was pretty accurate, but it didn't offend my wife and I near as much as them. I thought it was pretty good...what do you want for 37.5 pounds? Unfortunately I don't have any basis for comparison, but I can't imagine any of the other hotels in this price range being much better. If you're looking to spend your vacation dollars on something other than lodging, the Hotel Meridiana is a pretty safe way to go.	
